    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-11-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="459"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/379.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President stated in an interview that he considered the recent anti-American
                    demonstrations were simply a convenient cloak for Mexican revolutionists, who
                    are active in every part of the Republic. If any manifestations occur in the
                    future they will be mercilessly <pb facs="0441" n="359" xml:id="pg_359"/>
                    suppressed. He would be very grateful to the Government of the United States if
                    steps were taken to prevent the unlawful acts of the revolutionists who are
                    purchasing arms and ammunition in the United States.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
